 postsocialist villages in Eastern Europe and Asia illuminate the enduring importance of the house economy, which is based not on the market but on the order of the house. These formations show that economies depend not only on the macro institutions of markets and states but also on the micro institutions of families, communities, and house economies, often in an uneasy relationship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aHouseholdsxEconomic aspectszEurope, Eastern. 0aPost-communismzEurope, Eastern. 0aSelf-reliant livingzEurope, Eastern. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aCash, Jennifer R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGudeman, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGudeman, Stephen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHann, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHann, Chris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLight, Nathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonova, Miladina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTocheva, Detelina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVasile, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVidacs, Bea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782386964?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782386964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782386964/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL